window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>No rest for the wicked....</b></p> <p>Six months have passed since Asher Merrick and the Red Breakers saved Bouldergulf. Stronger than ever and training to hone his body, magic, and control over the Aura, Asher is finally starting to feel at home in the world of Echo Veil.</p> <p>But peace never lasts.</p> <p>When a noble from the Kingdom of Zala accuses the guild of murder and launches a devastating assault, Asher, Mara, Giezha, Kiersa, and Uli are forced into exile, along with the newest member of the team, Copper, a young dragon fiercely loyal to Asher and just as mischievous as he is deadly. Their escape leads them to Dellswreath, a town shrouded in shadow and plagued by a mysterious affliction known as The Shade.</p> <p>As darkness closes in and old tensions ignite, the Red Breakers uncover a conspiracy that threatens not only their lives but the fragile balance between kingdoms. To clear their names and stop a war, they'll have to cross deep into enemy territory and discover the dark truths at the heart of the unravelling conspiracy.</p> <p>Can Asher hold his team together, master the growing power within him, and protect the people he loves before the world burns?</p> <p>Reborn a Savior: Asher Merrick <i>is a thrilling, magic-fueled installment in the Reborn a Hero series. Packed with high-stakes adventure, dangerous discoveries, and the spicy, unconventional romance of Mara Brightwood, Uli Siannodel, Giezha Nightstrike, and Kiersa Denrel; this is the isekai fantasy you've been waiting for. Narrated in duet style.</i></p>"; 
